<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1589,1830]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
This species was described from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[636,731,1589,1614]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies" box="[747,995,1589,1614]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" refString="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y. (2004) A survey of the clearwing moths of the tribe Sesiini (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae) from Vietnam and adjacent countries with a synopsis of the Oriental Sesiini fauna. Tinea, 18 (1), 65 - 95." type="journal article" year="2004">
Kallies &amp; Arita 
<number box="[934,995,1590,1614]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Here we report it from 
<collectingCountry box="[1284,1351,1589,1614]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time. A single male was attracted to a strong mercury vapour light in the Nanling Mountains. It does not differ significantly from the Vietnamese specimens. This specimen represents the first record of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1299,1436,1661,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Sphecosesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Sphecosesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,284,1697,1722]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
. Other species recorded as 
<taxonomicName box="[590,727,1697,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Sphecosesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,727,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Sphecosesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[742,969,1698,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" refString="Yang, J. &amp; Wang, Y. (1989) A new genus and six species of clear-wings damaging forest and fruit tree. Forest Research, 2 (3), 229 - 238." type="journal article" year="1989">
Yang &amp; Wang 
<number box="[911,969,1698,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Xu" box="[981,1145,1697,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" refString="Xu, Z., Jin, T. &amp; Liu, X. (1999) Description of a new species of the genus Sphecosesia Hampson, 1910, from Jiangxi (Lep.: Sesiidae). Acta Agriculturae Boreali-occidentalis Sinica, 8 (2), 3 - 5." type="journal article" year="1999">
Xu 
<emphasis box="[1023,1080,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1087,1145,1698,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[1157,1345,1697,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" refString="Yang, L., Deng, G. R. &amp; Xian, Z. H. (2003) The relation between different longan varieties and their damage by Sphecosesia litchivora. Journal of South China Agricultural University, 24 (1), 30 - 33." type="journal article" year="2003">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[1223,1280,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1287,1345,1698,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[293,433,1734,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Teinotarsina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,433,1734,1757]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Teinotarsina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies" box="[553,792,1733,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" refString="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y. (2004) A survey of the clearwing moths of the tribe Sesiini (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae) from Vietnam and adjacent countries with a synopsis of the Oriental Sesiini fauna. Tinea, 18 (1), 65 - 95." type="journal article" year="2004">
